\c 3
\cl Hebrews 3
\cd Christ is more excellent than Moses: and therefore we must adhere to him by faith and obedience.
\p
\v 1 Wherefore, holy brethren, partakers of the heavenly vocation, consider the apostle and high priest of our profession, Jesus:
\p
\v 2 Who is faithful to him who appointed him, as was also *Moses in all his house.
\p
\v 3 For he was deemed worthy of greater glory than Moses, by so much as he who hath built the house, hath greater honour than the house.
\p
\v 4 For every house is built by some man: but he who created all things, is God.
\p
\v 5 And Moses indeed was faithful in all his house, as a servant, for a testimony of those things which were to be spoken:
\p
\v 6 But Christ, as a Son in his own house: which house are we, if we hold firm the confidence, and the glory of hope unto the end.
\p
\v 7 Wherefore, as the Holy Ghost saith: *To-day, if you shall hear his voice,
\p
\v 8 Harden not your hearts, as in the provocation, in the day of temptation in the desert,
\p
\v 9 Where your fathers tempted me, proved, and saw my works,
\p
\v 10 Forty years: For which cause I was offended with this generation, and I said: They always err in heart. And they have not known my ways,
\p
\v 11 As I have sworn in my wrath: If they shall enter into my rest.
\p
\v 12 Take heed, brethren, lest perhaps there be in any of you an evil heart of unbelief, to depart from the living God:
\p
\v 13 But exhort one another every day, whilst to-day is named: lest any one of you be hardened by the deceitfulness of sin.
\p
\v 14 For we are made partakers of Christ: yet so if we hold the beginning of his substance firm unto the end.
\p
\v 15 While it is said: To-day, if you shall hear his voice, harden not your hearts, as in that provocation.
\p
\v 16 For some who heard did provoke: but not all who came out of Egypt by Moses.
\p
\v 17 And with whom was he offended forty years? Was it not with those who sinned, *whose carcasses fell in the desert?
\p
\v 18 And to whom did he swear that they should not enter into his rest: but to them that believed not.
\p
\v 19 And we see that they could not enter in, because of unbelief.
